<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4b.12.9.001" />
<fw type="curatorial">14</fw>
<note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection [March 21, 1936]</note>
<fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
<fw type="authorial">Rec'd also request for two lectures in Spring &amp; summer. </fw>
<fw type="letterhead">ST. LOUIS POST-DISPATCH
EDITORIAL DEPARTMENT </fw>

<opener>
<dateline>Saturday 10:30 a.m. 
</dateline>
<salute>Dearest One:</salute>
</opener>

<p>Just heard that the "Friends of America Writers" Society has awarded me Honors and $100 for The
Messiah. I'm asked ot be in Chicago Apr. 15 &amp; receive the award, of possible. But I get the honor
&amp; money any way!</p>

<p>Also, I've just heard from Radio Station WBnX in New York, asking me to read my poetry there, or indicate what I want read. </p>

<p>I do love you, dearest one. I know this si not what Mrs. Boyles saw. There's more. 
It's for late April or early way.</p>

<closer>
<salute></salute>
<signed>Jno, Dad</signed>
<note></note>
</closer>

</div1>
</body>

